cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. Elvira prepares for her annual Halloween party by kidnapping Martha Stewart and holding her captive in a wooden crate.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Santa Claus Conquers The Martians
director: D.J. Viola, Stephen Chiodo, Nicholas Webster
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. Elvira celebrates Christmas with a stop-motion animated segment, a variety of puppets, stockings stuffed with amputees' legs, gingerdead men cookies and a special yuletide appearance by her longtime nemesis, The Breather.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Night Of The Living Dead
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. Elvira decides to clean out her basement, relaunch "Movie Macabre," and host "Night of the Living Dead."

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Manos: The Hands Of Fate
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. Elvira tries to elevate the material by hosting Manos as if it were an episode of Masterpiece Theater.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Lady Frankenstein
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. The son Elvira never knew she had abruptly appears and tries to take over her show.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: I Eat Your Skin
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. While hosting "I Eat Your Skin," Elvira complains that there's no actual flesh eating in the film, so she invents the I Eat Your Skin Diet and hawks Zombatrim pills.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Hercules And The Captive Women
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. Elvira's stuck hosting this Greek tragedy about Hercules and his voyage to Atlantis to rescue his son and battle an army of identical men and a strange up-right dragon.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Eegah
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. Elvira celebrates the achievements of "Eegah" (or lack thereof) by honoring the film at the Elvie Awards.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Don't Look In The Basement
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. While hosting "Don't Look in the Basement," Elvira hears radio reports of a deranged killer on the loose in her neighborhood.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Beast From Haunted Cave
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Attack Of The Giant Leeches
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark.

title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: A Bucket Of Blood
cast: Cassandra Peterson
description: A revamping, if you will, of the 1980's classic horror movie showcase, hosted by Elvira, Mistress of the Dark. Elvira tries her hand at being an artist in a variety of mediums. Also, Breather presents the Mistress of the Dark with The Publisher's Wet T-Shirt Contest Award.

title: Children of the Night
cast: Karen Black, Peter DeLuise, Ami Dolenz
description: A schoolteacher teams up with with a priest to stop a town being overrun by vampires.

title: Chhoto Bou
cast: Prosenjit Chatterjee, Devika Mukherjee, Ranjit Mallick, Sandhya Roy, Soham Chakraborty, Kali Banerjee, Meenakshi Goswami, Sanghamitra Bandyopadhyay, Ratna Ghoshal, Nimu Bhowmick
description: Mamta, Tandra, and Deepa live with their mother-in-law, who likes Tandra as her husband earns the most. Mamta and Deepa take more care of her, yet she does not appreciate them, until she falls ill and the money for her operation is given by them.

title: Blood Crime
cast: James Caan, Johnathon Schaech, Elizabeth Lackey
description: A thriller about a cop who flees the big city with his wife for a better life in a small town. After making the move, the wife is brutally assaulted on the same night the son of the local sheriff is killed. The local officer and the big city cop are then forced to find the perpetrators together.

title: Two Cents From a Pariah
cast: Jeffrey Grover, Cortney Palm, Mark Grossman, Charlie Berens, Jade Elysan, Kelsey Boze, Ali Ryan, Marisa Roper, Lucas Veltrie, Terence Hall, Dena Tyler, Roy James Wilson
description: All is perfect for Donovan Strathmore, lifecoach to the rich and famous, until a mysterious figure emerges, threatening to reveal a hidden past. As he searches for clues, his life begins to unravel, culminating in an onslaught of public humiliation. Donovan is forced to reconcile secrets long buried, and confront the one person he's spent his life running from.

title: The Waterfall Murder
cast: Manuel Rubey, Stefanie Reinsperger, Gerhard Greiner, Patricia Aulitzky
description: A young girl is found dead in a waterfall with a heart-shaped stone in her hand. The investigation leads to an esoteric cult: The Dragon Maiden.

title: The Last Party
cast: Robert Downey Jr., Mary Stuart Masterson, Oliver Stone, Sean Penn, Jerry Brown, Al Sharpton
description: Searching for answers about politics and government, Robert Downey Jr. takes to the streets to examine the 1992 presidential campaign from a youthful perspective.

title: Tangerines
cast: Lambit Ulfsak, Elmo Nuganen, Giorgi Nakashidze
description: The war rages in Georgia, an Estonian man stays behind to harvest his crop of tangerines.The war arrives at his door.

title: Reel Injun
description: Cree filmmaker Neil Diamond takes an entertaining and insightful look at the portrayal of North American Indigenous people throughout a century of cinema. Featuring hundreds of clips from old classics as well as recent releases, candid interviews with celebrities like Clint Eastwood, Robbie Robertson and Jim Jarmusch, the film traces the evolution of the Hollywood Indian.

title: Chiara Ferragni: Unposted [English Dubbed]
cast: Chiara Ferragni
description: [Dubbed in English. Original Version also available – search: Chiara Unposted Subbed] Chiara Ferragni, the first fashion influencer in the world, reveals how the digital revolution has disrupted the worlds of business, communication, fashion, and culture, through a portrait in which she's the protagonist – both as a woman and as digital entrepreneur.

title: Best Night Ever
cast: Desiree Hall, Samantha Colburn, Eddie Ritchard, Crista Flanagan
description: Bride-to-be Claire, her sister Leslie, fun-loving Zoe, and quirky new friend Janet set off to Las Vegas for a one-night bachelorette party that turns out to be more than they bargained for.

title: Zana
cast: Adriana Matoshi, Astrit Kabashi, Fatmire Sahiti, Mensur Safqiu, Vedat Bajrami, Irena Cahani, Shengyl Ismaili, Bislim Muçaj, Çun Lajçi, Ilire Vinca Celaj
description: Haunted by her long suppressed past and pressured by family to seek treatment from mystical healers for her infertility, a Kosovar woman struggles to reconcile the expectations of motherhood with a legacy of wartime brutality.

title: What Have We Done to Deserve This?
cast: Caroline Peters, Chantal Zitzenbacher, Simon Schwarz
description: Wanda's world has been turned upside down when her teenage daughter Nina suddenly turns up in a hijab. Nina has secretly converted to Islam.

title: We Had it Coming
cast: Natalie Krill, Alexia Fast, Erin Agostino, Vanessa Smythe, Nabil Khatib
description: Anna looks to avenge her sister's suicide to the hands of a dangerous Pimp. In the process, she encounters a mysterious female recruiter of younger more vulnerable girls.

title: Two Worlds Colliding
description: When Night comes forward with his story of being dumped by two police officers in -20 C temperatures in a barren field on the city outskirts, he sets into motion a chain of events: a major RCMP investigation into several suspicious deaths, the conviction of the two constables who abandoned him and the reopening of an old case, leading to a judicial inquiry.

title: TREASURE 8
cast: Jonathan Brook
description: From their headquarters in the Bay Area, Treasure 8 is aiming to revolutionise the global food system, using technology to reduce food waste, lower the cost of nutrition and increase food security worldwide. One of their technological approaches dehydrates food while maintaining most of its nutrients; not just cutting waste but reducing also emissions on shipping and lowering costs to consumers.

title: The Wrong Path
cast: C. Thomas Howell, Drew Moerlein, Abigail Hawk, Gene Gabriel, Vince Oddo, Sal Rendino, Artie Pasquale, Joe D'Onofrio, Christopher Brian Roach
description: A small town electrician with anger issues gets extreme therapy from a noted Pyschiatrist, Dr. Eric Poslowe, but is soon framed for a robbery and then a murder. Even with the help of Dr. Poslowe's female assistant Bonnie, he soon learns to trust no one but himself and becomes entrapped in a web of deceit, greed and corruption.

title: The Swindlers
cast: Hyun Bin, Ji-tae Yu, Seong-woo Bae, Sung-woong Park
description: High stakes and fast talk are the game in this crime caper where allies from different sides of the law must work together to trap the world's most legendary con man.

title: The Minis
cast: Dennis Rodman, Gabriel Pimentel, Joe Gnoffo, Richard Portnow
description: A talented team of basketball players made up of little people enters a tournament to help a teammate's son go to college.

title: The Boss and the Worker
description: Social/sexual farce focusing on a boss and his workers in a faucet factory.

title: Tempest Eye
cast: Avery Kidd Waddell, Susan Traylor, Duane Whitaker, Eric Michael Cole, Bentley Mitchum
description: A man with amnesia is a suspect in a murder case, while the lead detective and his therapist are his only chance of freedom, he battles with mental health issues.

title: Steal This Movie
cast: Vincent D'Onofrio, Janeane Garofalo, Jeanne Tripplehorn
description: A unique journey into the life of activist and radical Abbie Hoffman (Vincent D'Onofrio), as he battles for social justice and travels through the maze of music and politics that defined the late sixties and early seventies.

title: Simha (Kannada)
cast: Nandamuri Balakrishna, Nayanthara, Sneha Ullal, Brahmanandam, Namitha
description: Srimann Narayana is a college professor who's hot-blooded by nature & doesn't tolerate injustice. New student, Janaki joins his college & falls in love with him. Janaki has a violent past,which is closely linked to Srimann's own past. Srimann Narayana's grandmother narrates about his past, his father & his family. What is his past? How his past affects his present & how he clears his issues?

title: Senior Entourage
cast: Ed Asner, Mark Rydell, Helen Reddy, Marion Ross, Charles Robinson, David A. Lockhart, Brian Connors
description: A wild, wacky "Mockumentary" comedy featuring a zany, multi-racial cast ranging in age from 9 to 90. It's "Seinfeld for seniors" starring Ed Asner, Helen Reddy, Charlie Robinson, Marion Ross and Mark Rydell.

title: Open Door
cast: Luli Bitri, Jonida Vokshi, Gulielm Radoja, Sotiraq Bratko
description: Married Rudina sets off on a long journey with her pregnant sister, Elma, to meet their strict, traditional father in the Albanian village where they were born. As Rudina's car makes its way across the mountains, Elma comes up with a plan to enlist an ex-classmate to play the part of her husband.

title: One Step From Me
cast: Johanna Solano, Esteban Hidalgo, Gustavo Rojas
description: Tatiana is a journalist with a routine life in all its aspects and a recent failed love relationship. Motivated by her best friend, she decides to make a stop and travel around Costa Rica to find herself and inner peace.

title: McCanick
cast: Cory Monteith, David Morse, Mike Vogel, Rachel Nichols
description: Set over the course of one day, a narcotics detective hunts for a seemingly harmless young criminal who knows a truth about the cop's past.

title: Martha of the North
description: In the mid-1950s, lured by false promises of a better life, Inuit families were displaced by the Canadian government and left to their own devices in the Far North. In this icy desert realm, Martha Flaherty and her family lived through one of Canadian history's most sombre and little-known episodes.

title: Life on the Rocks
director: Joanna Bowzer, Tim Gagliardo, Barry Pollack, Tim Russ, Shae-Lee Shakleford
cast: Bonnie Bedelia, Ray Wise, Elester Latham, Ally Iseman, Jessica Lynn Parsons
description: Five Directors tell Five Stories. We meet their "characters" at a local bar - where they find love, misfortune and redemption.

title: Let Me Be Frank
cast: Freddy Andreiuci, Ryan Silva, Lora Lee, Lara Ingraham, Michael Casey, Jared Scott
description: A young rapper moves to Los Angeles in search of stardom and instead finds an unlikely friend in his dispirited apartment manager whose dreams led him to the same city twenty years prior.

title: LEGO Monkie Kid: A Hero Is Born
cast: Jack De Sena, Dave B. Mitchell, Stephanie Sheh, David Chen, Sean Schemmel, Patrick Seitz
description: After the release of the Demon Bull King, MK accidentally grabs Monkey King's magical staff and goes on a journey to return the staff to Monkey King

title: JJ Barrows: Doodle All Day
cast: JJ Barrows
listed_in: Arts, Entertainment, and Culture, Comedy, Special Interest
description: JJ Barrows was raised in South Carolina as the middle child of a preacher's family. Having always felt a little different, JJ uses humor to navigate through the realities of life, being single through her thirties, and adjusting to life changes brought about by age, a cross country move, and eventually.

title: Jeff Allen: I Can Laugh About it Now
cast: Jeff Allen
listed_in: Arts, Entertainment, and Culture, Comedy, Special Interest
description: Jeff Allen combines clean, hilarious humor like no other comedian working today. Besides performing at corporate functions and fundraisers, he regularly appears on television, radio, and casinos across the country.

title: Halloween Heroes
cast: Bobby Lacer, James Dickey, Eileen Lacer, Brayden Lacer
description: When a group of teens become magically infused with the powers of their Halloween costumes, they band together to investigate several local spooky legends. Will these haunted folk tales wind up getting the better of them?

title: Finding Dawn
description: Filmmaker Christine Welsh brings us a compelling documentary that puts a human face on a national tragedy -the epidemic of missing or murdered Indigenous women in Canada. The film takes a journey into the heart of these women's experience, from Vancouver's skid row, down the Highway of Tears in northern BC, and on to Saskatoon, where the murders and disappearances of these women remain unsolved.

title: Eddie Izzard: Dress To Circle
cast: Eddie Izzard
listed_in: Arts, Entertainment, and Culture, Comedy, Special Interest
description: A one-hour rough-cut of Eddie Izzard's Dress To Kill show in Paris (spoken in French). Previously released on the Dress To Kill DVD.

title: Chinese Speaking Vampires
cast: Davy Williams, Chris Cleveland, Crystal Huang, Jerimiyah Dunbar, June Lee, Raven Armando Astone
description: A desperate actor becomes a vampire and uses his new powers to land a movie role and the girl, but then must choose between life and the undead.

title: Cerebrum
cast: James Russo, Alexxis Lemire, Christian James, Anirudh Pisharody
description: To make ends meet, Tom signs on as a guinea pig at a home-based lab, but when he commits a crime he cannot remember, he must risk his own sanity to reveal the truth.

title: BoBoiBoy: Elemental Heroes
cast: Nur Fathiah Diaz, Nizam Razak, Ieesya Isandra, Anas Abdul Aziz, Nur Sarah Alisya, Yap Ee Jean
description: BoBoiBoy and his friends have been attacked by a villain named Retak'ka who is the original user of BoBoiBoy's elemental powers. He seeks to take back his elemental powers from BoBoiBoy to become the most powerful person and dominate the galaxy. Together with his friends, BoBoiBoy must find a way to defeat Retak'ka before his powers fall into the wrong hands.

title: Blunderpuss
cast: Chris Manley, Jeff Seal, Drae Campbell, Karolena Theresa, Mona Chalabi, Danny Manley, Norah Manley, Meg Anderson
description: Mike Bruton is a clown with a drinking problem. Seriously – a real clown. Eager to pick up where he left off after a stint in rehab, Mike hops on his unicycle and takes off on an apology tour, starting with a visit to his childhood home in New Jersey and ending up in Brooklyn. Mike soon realizes that not everyone is ready to forgive him and his best bet at a life in recovery is to start small.

title: Blue Call
cast: Katie Leclerc, Jonathan Bennett, Jack McGee, Andrea Sixtos, William Belli, Shelby Wulfurt
description: AN lEMT suffering from PTSD Spends her days making split second decisions with lives that hang in the balance. One night on a routine call, she is faced with a moral decision, taking matters into her own hands and mercy kills a young woman. Now, falling deeper and deeper into a rabbit hole, she gets caught up in a world of underground drugs and a sadistic killer who's made her his next victim.

title: Blind Ghost
cast: Alix Villaret, Tim Dax, Lindsey Sirera, Casey Graf, Jeremiah Benjamin
description: A blind young woman receives an experimental surgery to restore her vision which also conjures dark spirits.

title: Bicycle Kick
cast: Ritwik Chakraborty, Ridhima Ghosh, Sourav Banerjee, Soumitra Chatterjee
description: When a football coach meets a gifted footballer who could not make his mark on the sport due to an unforeseen trauma, he decides to find a way to get the young man back into the game.

title: Battered
cast: Mia Paris, Carly Jones, Luke Banham, Laura Lee, Charles A. Baird, Spencer Kane, Marc Bilker, Bianca Conner, Jim LeVasseur, Helen Wilson, Stacy Firkus, Molly Monroe, T. Patrick Quinn
description: After Piper's alcoholic boyfriend sends her to the hospital, she joins a group of battered women who decide to kill their exes, only to discover that these guys won't go down without a fight.

title: American Masters: Raul Julia: The World's a Stage
cast: Anjelica Huston, Edward James Olmos, Rita Moreno, James Earl Jones, Sonia Braga, Rubén Blades, Esai Morales, John Leguizamo, Jimmy Smits, Andy Garcia
description: Raúl Juliá: The World’s A Stage examines the life and career of entertainer Raúl Juliá. The documentary is a revealing portrait of the actor, who earned recognition for his versatility on stage and on screen.

title: All Creatures Here Below
cast: Karen Gillan, David Dastmalchian, Jennifer Morrison, David Koechner, Richard Cabral
description: Gensan (David Dastmalchian) and Ruby (Karen Gillan) struggle in the face of poverty which is made worse when Gensan loses his job. Forced to break the law to make ends meet, he sets out on the run with Ruby across the country hoping to finally find their freedom.

title: Adrift in Soho
cast: Caitlin Harris, Chris Wellington, Emily Seale-Jones, Lauren Harris, Owen Drake
description: A philosopher and a group of filmmakers begin a new era. Soho in the 1950s where the seeds of the 1960s were sown. Adrift In Soho takes an uncompromising look at what really happened in the decade where it all began.

title: Adam and Evelyn
cast: Anne Kanis, Florian Teichtmeister, Lena Lauzemis
description: An East German couple is looking for their way of life after the political situation drastically changes by the fall of the Wall in 1989. Adam and Evelyn have to decide in which world - Eastern or Western - they want to live in order to find a happy life.

title: Acting Out
cast: Victoria Corsaut, Michael Gaunt
description: Before the dawn of reality T. V., the film Acting Out showed everyday people revealing their most private fantasies. Ten people were selected after answering an ad in Gallery Magazine. From there, they were provided with a naked cast, a private setting and film crew. In front of the cameras and without a script, they were given the opportunity to "act out" their sexually deviant dreams.

title: Write to Kill
cast: Scott Valentine, Joan Severance, Chris Mulkey
description: A writer is framed for murder while investigating his brother's death.

title: Windcroft
cast: Joe Ryan, Vanessa Daniels, Monica Knight, Ray Wasik, Amanda Renee Knox
description: On a remote farm in the sweeping hills of Pennsylvania, three lives are torn apart by love, abandonment, deception and murder. After the death of his father, John and his new wife, Diane, arrive to claim the estate - but, John's father bequeathed to him more than just the family farm, and he is forced to face a heritage of madness and violence.

title: What Makes a Family
cast: Brooke Shields, Cherry Jones, Anne Meara
description: Based on a true story of two women who form a partnership and eventually have a child. When the biological mother is stricken with a fatal disease, her partner discovers she has no legal rights to the child. This heartwarming story examines our cultural and legal perceptions of what makes a family.

title: What Is My Name
cast: Konstantin Lavronenko, Alexandra Bortich, Marina Vasilieva, Kirill Kaganovich
description: 17-year-old Muscovites Olya and Sasha go to Crimea to meet Olya's father Sergei. Sergei has lived all his life in a small seaside village and has never seen his only daughter. On the threshold of his house, Olya is frightened of the upcoming meeting and asks Sasha to "change places." Sasha introduces herself as Olya, that is, her daughter, and Olya pretends to be her friend.

title: Viyabari
cast: S. J. Surya, Tamannaah, Namitha, Vadivelu, Santhanam
description: Suryaprakash, an ambitious businessman, wishes to accumulate a lot of wealth for himself. He asks a scientist to clone him to replace him at home, while he gives his time to his business.

title: Vivaramana Aalu
cast: Sathyaraj, Devayani, Mumtaj, Vivek
description: Mayilsamy, a thief, deserts his wife Pappu when he meets a rich woman. When he realises his mistake, he comes back to Pappu and must win her trust once again.

title: Uptown Girls
cast: Brittany Murphy, Dakota Fanning, Donald Faison, Heather Locklear, Marley Shelton
description: Molly Gunn (Brittany Murphy, Clueless) is the freewheeling daughter of a late rock legend, and the toast of the New York City social scene. But when her inheritance is stolen, Molly is forced to do something she's never done before – she's forced to get a job. Molly becomes a nanny to a precocious little girl, who is "eight going on forty."

title: Untamed Heart
cast: Christian Slater, Marisa Tomei, Rosie Perez, Kyle Secor, Willie Garson, James Cada, Gary Groomes
description: Two of today's hottest young actors, Christian Slater and Marisa Tomei, star in this tender romance about lonely souls destined to find one another. Co-starring Rosie Perez.

title: Unsurety
cast: Kandace Burnett, Deonde Crawford, Janeshia Wilson, Kejuan Moses, Thomas Hanks
description: Olivia Moore is a broken, hardworking, single parent who supports her daughter by running an outpatient clinic, where she is reconnected with ex-NFL player Corey Mack As Olivia makes efforts to allow her heart to be mended by Corey, adversity settles in.

title: Universal Soldier
cast: Jean-Claude Van Damme, Dolph Lundgren, Ed O'Ross, Ally Walker, Jerry Orbach
description: Luc Devreaux (Jean-Claude Van Damme) and Sgt. Andrew Scott (Dolph Lundgren) are two soldiers who kill each other in Vietnam and are brought back to life 25 years later for a secret government program.

title: Tuck Jagadish (Tamil)
cast: Nani, Ritu Varma, Aishwarya Rajesh, Jagapathi Babu, Daniel Balaji, Nasser, Parvathi T, Rohini, Rao Ramesh, Naresh
description: When a doting elder brother has a dispute with the younger one over the inheritance, the latter tries to establish peace and keep the family together.

title: Troll
cast: Michael Moriarty, Julia Louis-Dreyfus, Noah Hathaway, Sonny Bono, Shelley Hack, Jenny Beck, Phil Fondacaro, Gary Sandy, Anne Lockhart
description: When an evil troll named Torok attempts to bring about cataclysmic changes that will forever erase mankind, an ancient sorceress and a young boy join forces to stop him before he can carry out his diabolical plan.

title: Topkapi
cast: Melina Mercouri, Peter Ustinov, Maximilian Schell, Robert Morley, Jess Hahn, Gilles Ségal
description: Peter Ustinov won an Oscar for Best Supporting Actor in director Jules Dassin's lighthearted thriller about five thieves (including Melina Mercouri, Maximilian Schell and Robert Morley) who undertake an "absolutely impossible" grand theft in Istanbul.

title: Things You Can Tell Just By Looking At Her
cast: Glenn Close, Cameron Diaz, Calista Flockhart, Kathy Baker, Amy Brenneman, Valeria Golino, Holly Hunter
description: Set in Los Angeles, tells five loosely related stories about the loves and losses in the lives of five women.

title: The Whereabouts of Jenny
cast: Ed O'Neill, Debrah Farentino, Eve Gordon, David Graf
description: This powerful, heart-wrenching story about Jimmy O'Meara (Ed O'Neill), who discovers that his ex-wife has married an ex-drug dealer turned government informer, making him eligible for the witness relocation program. With his daughter in mind, Jimmy is determined to find the whereabouts of Jenny.

title: The Thing (2011)
cast: Mary Elizabeth Winstead, Joel Edgerton, Adewale Akinnuoye-Agbaje, Ulrich Thomsen, Eric Christian Olsen, Trond Espen Seim
description: HD. A team of scientists uncover a shape-shifting monster in remote Antarctica in this prequel to John Carpenter's 'The Thing.'

title: The Squid And The Whale
cast: Jesse Eisenberg, Laura Linney, Jeff Daniels
description: In his third feature, director Noah Baumbach scores a triumph with an autobiographical coming-of-age story about a teenager whose writer-parents are divorcing. The father (Jeff Daniels) and mother (Laura Linney) duke it out in half-civilized, half-savage fashion, while their two sons adapt in different ways, shifting allegiances between parents. The film is squirmy-funny and nakedly honest ab..

title: The Sneak Over
cast: Reed Taylor, Will Hyde, Max Purget, Michael Hodges, Katie Burgess, Connie Franklin, Cassie Self, Brian Shoop
description: It's the summer before fifth grade and Henry Hudson hasn't found his place in the world. Then he meets a group of immature film geeks who give him the courage to lead a battle against the neighborhood bullies and finally become one of the guys.

title: The Rookies
cast: Talu Wang, Milla Jovovich, Sandrine Pinna, David Lee McInnis
description: Extreme sport lover Zhou Feng got involved in an international illegal trade by accident. So he had to follow an international special agent Bruce to Budapest.

title: The Rage: Carrie 2
cast: Amy Irving, Dylan Bruno, Emily Bergl, J. Smith-Cameron, Jason London
description: Rachel (Emily Bergl) is a high school misfit who gets caught in the middle of a prank orchestrated by a group of jocks a prank that turns deadly.

title: The Pudgie Movie
cast: Designer, Ameir White
description: A hilarious inner city comedy about a young man trying to fit in.

title: The Outer Darkness
cast: David Blood, Anita Booth, Isla Carter, Anthony Edridge
description: On Friday evenings in Lynnsmouth Community Centre, meets a group led by Father Jonathan Crowe. Together they share their stories - tales of strange occurrences, horrific events and bizarre encounters that have scarred their lives. Tonight, a young tormented woman called Jenny will share a story of her experience with a game of chance that sealed the fate of her family... Presented by ALTER.

title: The Organization
cast: Sidney Poitier, Barbara McNair, Gerald S. O'Loughlin, Sheree North, Fred Beir, Allen Garfield, Bernie Hamilton, Graham Jarvis, Raul Julia
description: The dangerous world of international heroin trafficking is exposed in this elaborate and suspenseful crime thriller which reprises Sidney Poitier's role as Lt. Virgil Tibbs.

title: The Midnight After
cast: Simon Yam, Tien You Chui
description: On a night just like any other, a minibus full of passengers drives through a tunnel and arrives in another dimension; the eclectic group of passengers seek refuge in a deserted cafe and make a horrific discovery.

title: The Michelle Apartments
cast: Henry Czerny, Mary Elizabeth Rubens, Daniel Kash
description: A straight-laced tax man (Henry Czerny) sent to audit the crooked books of a small town chemical company gets intertwined with lust and corruption when drawn to a seductress (Mary Elizabeth Rubens), her violent husband (Daniel Kash), and other weird tenants of Michelle Apartments.

title: The Life Aquatic with Steve Zissou
cast: Bill Murray, Owen Wilson, Cate Blanchett, Anjelica Huston, Willen Dafoe, Jeff Goldblum, Michael Gambon, Bud Cort
description: An oceanographer sets out after the shark that killed his partner.

title: The Joyriders
cast: Martin Landau, Kris Kristofferson, Shawn Hatosy, Elisabeth Moss
description: A suicidal older man, Gordon Trout, is kidnapped for his car and money by three runaway teenagers who live on the streets. Their experiences together make them a close-knit family, but the nature of the crime committed could tear them apart. The intricacies of these complex relationships are explored through an emotional story with twists and turns.

title: The Grudge 2
cast: Amber Tamblyn, Arielle Kebbel, Jennifer Beals, Edison Chen, Sarah Roemer, Sarah Michelle Gellar
description: Acclaimed producers Sam Raimi, Rob Tapert and Taka Ichise have re-teamed with director Takashi Shimizu and screenwriter Stephen Susco to present this heart-stopping sequel to the smash-hit thriller, The Grudge.

title: The Great Train Robbery
cast: Sean Connery, Donald Sutherland, Lesley-Anne Down
description: Sean Connery, Donald Sutherland and Lesley-Anne Down star in this true-life action thriller, based on director/screenwriter Michael Crichton's best-selling novel, about a daring gold heist that shocked Victorian society.

title: The Great Hypnotist
cast: Jing Hu, Zhong Lu, Karen Mok
description: Ren sees dead people, and it's driving her mad. She's also demonstrating psychic abilities, but psychiatrist Xu Ruining thinks it's a hoax, and his radical new therapy could uncover the truth - through experimental hypnosis.

title: The Graduate
cast: Dustin Hoffman, Anne Bancroft, Katharine Ross, Norman Fell, William Daniels, Murray Hamilton, Elizabeth Wilson, Brian Avery, Walter Brooke
description: Hollywood darlings Dustin Hoffman, Anne Bancroft and Katharine Ross create one outrageous love triangle in this groundbreaking American film classic.

title: The Forest Killer
cast: Miriam Stein, Hary Prinz, Thomas Stipsits, August Schmölzer
description: A young police detective is assigned to a brutal murder case in her hometown. When her brother becomes the prime suspect, she is forced to confront the demons of her past.

title: The Crocodile Hunter: Collision Course
cast: Steve Irwin, Magda Szubanski, David Wenham, Terri Irwin
description: Aussie adventurer Steve Irwin – a.k.a. "The Crocodile Hunter" – has avoided the death-roll and nabbed another feisty croc, hoping to save it from poachers. What Steve doesn't know is that the crocodile has innocently swallowed a top secret U.S. satellite beacon, and the poachers are actually American special agents sent to retrieve it. Crikey!

title: The Comedy of Terrors
cast: Vincent Price, Peter Lorre, Boris Karloff, Joyce Jameson, Joe E. Brown, Basil Rathbone
description: Vincent Price stars as Waldo Trumbull, a lazy New England funeral parlor owner, who blackmails Peter Lorre into helping him increase business by killing people. Price meets resistance from his landlord (Basil Rathbone), wife and senile old father-in-law (Boris Karloff).

title: The Burning Bed
cast: Farrah Fawcett, Paul Le Mat, Richard Masur, Grace Zabriskie, Penelope Milford, James Callahan
description: A battered wife sets her husband on fire one night after living with his beatings and humiliations for years.

title: The Brain (1988)
cast: Tom Bresnahan, Cynthia Preston, David Gale
description: With the help of an alien organism, a man brainwashes audiences through television; a troubled high school student is determined to stop them.

title: The Boat
cast: Joe Azzopardi
description: A solo sailor is locked inside the head of a sailboat which is under steam on autopilot.

title: The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel
cast: Tom Wilkinson, Bill Nighy
description: British pensioners on a tight budget move to a retirement home in india; their adventures there giving them a new lease on life.

title: The Bad News Bears (1976)
cast: Walter Matthau, Tatum O'Neal, Vic Morrow, Joyce Van Patten
description: A beer-guzzling ex-minor leaguer reluctantly agrees to coach a bunch of clumsy, misfit Little League baseball players to compete for a high-stakes championship in California.

title: That Day We Sang
cast: Michael Ball, Imelda Staunton
listed_in: Arts, Entertainment, and Culture, Drama, Romance
description: This musical rooted in Manchester in 1969 tells the story of two lonely middle-aged people who are able to grab a second chance at life, reconnected to their emotions by the power of music.

title: Terror in a Texas Town
cast: Sterling Hayden, Carol Kelly
description: A greedy financier and a gang of gunmen force people to sell land.

title: Ten Minutes to Midnight
cast: Caroline Williams, Nicole Kang, Nicholas Tucci, William Youmans, Adam Weppler, Alice Kremelberg, Greg Balla
description: A veteran late night radio host on the eve of forced retirement is trapped inside the station after being bitten by a rabid bat while her mysterious replacement follows her every move.

title: Taller Than The Trees
cast: S. Joshua Costantini, Quinn Costantini, Cricket Costantini, Loren Costantini, Dean Tucker, Monica Costantini, Calder Costantini, Mona Costantini, Jason Costantini
description: A man embarks on a mysterious journey deep into the wilderness in search of the one thing he's been studying his entire life. Meanwhile, his daughter knows something he doesn't and is in pursuit to track him down and stop him from the point of no return.

title: Taken
cast: Liam Neeson, Famke Janssen, Leland Orser, Radivoje Bukvic, Mathieu Busson, Holly Valance, Katie Cassidy, Xander Berkeley, Nicolas Giraud, Maggie Grace, Jon Gries, Michael Mandaville, Luc Besson, Robert Mark Kamen, Christophe Kourotchkine, Valentin Kalaj, Nabil Massad, Jalil Naciri, Edwin Kruger, Olivier Rabourdin, Anca Radici, Christy Reese, Nathan Rippy, Opender Singh, Helena Soubeyrand, Tommy Spahija, Anatole Taubman, Bertrand Treuil, George Hertzberg, David Warshofsky, Ivette Gonzalez, Gerard Watkins, Don Abernathy, Pierre Morel, Didier Hoarau, Franck Lebreton
description: When his estranged daughter is kidnapped in Paris, a former spy (Liam Neeson) sets out to find her at any cost. Relying on his special skills, he tracks down the ruthless gang that abducted her and launches a one-man war to bring them to justice and rescue his daughter.

title: Swimming for Gold
cast: Peyton List, Daniel Needs
description: A US women’s swim team Olympic hopeful suffers an injury that forces her to put aside her dreams and help the Australian men’s swim team get competition ready.

title: Summer Rebels
cast: Eliáš Vyskocil, Pavel Nový, Liana Pavlíková
description: Jonas wants to visit his cool grandpa for a summer of fun on the river, but his mom has other plans. Undeterred, Jonas takes off on an adventure of his own in this tale of rebellion, friendship, catastrophe and, ultimately, redemption.

title: Sugar Hill
cast: Marki Bey, Don Pedro Colley, Robert Quarry, Zara Cully, Charles Robinson, Betty Anne Rees, Richard Lawson
description: Pray you never cross a woman out for revenge and her squad of zombie hitmen! When a nightclub entrepreneur gets taken out by the mob, his girlfriend, Diana "Sugar" Hill, calls upon the voodoo high priest Baron Samedi to summon up the undead to carry out an unholy plan for revenge. Packed with horror, action, and loads of 70s funk, "Sugar Hill" will slay you! Starring Robert Quarry and Zara Cully.

title: Sudden Terror: The Hijacking of Schoolbus 17
cast: Maria Conchita Alonso, Marcy Walker, Michael Paul Chan
description: A chilling story of a courageous school bus driver's nerve shattering ordeal confronting a deranged hijacker who seizes command of her busload of mentally challenged youngsters. Meanwhile, Lt. Kathy Leone and Lt. Dominick Caroselli attempt to stay one step ahead of the hijacker's lethal plan and plot the rescue of the hostages.

title: Stormy Weathers
cast: Cybill Shepherd, Robert Beltran, Charlie Schlatter
description: Samantha "Sam" Weathers, armed with a black belt in karate and a wisecracking view of life, is a police officer's daughter, who has a love for L.A.'s opulence, tempered with a knowledge of its lethal undercurrents. Things start to sizzle when an Italian aristocrat hires her to track down a missing relative.

title: Still of the Night
cast: Roy Scheider, Meryl Streep, Jessica Tandy, Irving Metzmen, Joe Grifasi
description: Roy Scheider and Meryl Streep star in a highly charged, Hitchcock- inspired murder mystery set among New York's chic world of high- rolling antique brokers. Co-stars Jessica Tandy.

title: Stargate
cast: Kurt Russell, James Spader, Jaye Davidson, Viveca Lindfors, John Diehl
description: When an ancient Egyptian artifact is discovered, two men unlock its secret power as a portal through time and space.

title: Starblack
cast: Robert Woods, Elga Andersen
description: Starblack is a hero who dresses in black and his face is covered by a black scarf and he carries in his shirt a black star, which he always leaves at the scene of his enterprises, as a symbol of justice.

title: Squirm
cast: Don Scardino, Fran Higgins, Jean Sullivan, Patricia Pearcy, Peter MacLean, R.A. Dow
description: During the worst electrical storm in the history of a small fishing village in Georgia, a power line topples near a worm farm and electro- cutes the bugs. The electrified worms turn into man-eaters, devouring everything in their path!

title: Snow
cast: Lambert Loeffen, Sonny Bakic, Catherine Mazer
description: Isolated in the vast oil fields of the Canadian North is a tiny town of Zama, with a population of only two hundred. The cold, the darkness and the isolation effect each one in different ways, where sometimes the distinction between what is real and surreal disappear.

title: Sleepaway Camp II: Unhappy Campers
cast: Brian Patrick Clarke, Valerie Hartman, Pamela Springsteen, Tony Higgins, Renee Estevez, Walter Gotell
description: The grisly murders that terrorized Camp Arawak have become favorite ghost stories around Camp Rolling Hills six years later. As each of the campers learn the secrets about the murders, their carefree days at summer camp come to an end.

title: Sign of the Gladiator
cast: Anita Ekberg, Georges Marchal, Folco Lulli
description: Zenobia, Queen of Palmira, revolts against Rome and defeats the Roman troops but she makes a big mistake when she falls in love with enemy officer Marco Valerio.

title: Shots Fired
cast: Black Jack Johnson, Will Cummings III, Carmelo Giangrande, Jay Davis
description: An action-packed comedy about two opposite detectives, forced to work together. Kevin, a burned out, thrill-seeker, has cost the city millions. Marcus, a weed-smoking, alcoholic who's had his uncle/captain, reprimanded him on several occasions. Both these men have differences but they somehow work with each other to solve the biggest case of their careers.

title: She Never Died
cast: Olunike Adeliyi, Peter MacNeill, Kiana Madeira, Noah Dalton Danby
description: Lacey, a socially detached loner is cursed with immortality and a never-ending tedium of existence. In her attempts to keep her compulsions in check, she seeks out the darkest souls humanity has to offer. Lacey must now face her own inner demons while simultaneously finding her next meal.

title: Sea Ghost
cast: William Warlock, Michael Rogers, Warren Christie, Catherine Lough Haggquist, Kurt Max Runte, Peter Graham-Gaudreau
description: A secret drilling platform in the Gulf of Mexico retrieves a dormant alien creature from the bottom of the ocean. It soon awakens and goes on a telepathic rampage.

title: Scream and Scream Again

description: A deranged scientist, seeking to create a race of super humans by means of organic transplant, commits a series of brutal murders in order to utilize the bodies. Screen and horror legends Vincent Price, Christopher Lee and Peter Cushing star!

title: Scorpio
cast: Burt Lancaster, Alain Delon, Paul Scofield, John Colicos, Gayle Hunnicutt, J.D. Cannon, Joanne Linville
description: In a chilling scenario of international espionage and intrigue, Burt Lancaster and Alain Delon star as two adversaries, one a C.I.A. agent, the other a French assassin hired to kill him.

title: Scarecrows
cast: David James Campbell, Michael Simms, Mike Balog, Richard Vidan, Ted Vernon
description: Five crooks rob an army base payroll and kidnap a pilot and his daughter, who are forced to fly them to Mexico. One crook parachutes out with the money – followed closely by the others. All five land in a mysterious, abandoned graveyard at night, where they are terrorized by ghouls.

title: Saving Mr. Wu
cast: Andy Lau, Ye Liu
description: Four devious criminals, one chilling scam: pose as cops, kidnap a victim, and if no ransom comes in 24 hours, the target dies. Tonight they caught a movie star (Andy Lau) and the countdown begins.

title: Salvador
cast: James Woods, Jim Belushi, Michael Murphy, John Savage, Elpidia Carrillo, Tony Plana, Colby Chester, Cynthia Gibb
description: Compelling drama based on the real experiences of journalist Richard Boyle in strife-ridden El Salvador in 1980-81.

title: Saginaw Trail
cast: Gene Autry, Champion, Connie Marshall
description: Gene Autry is sent to investigate the murders of settlers with the help of Smiley Burnette and two young homesteaders. Gene soon discovers that rich fur trader is behind the staged Indian raids.

title: Rugrats Go Wild
cast: Elizabeth Daily, Nancy Cartwright, Kath Soucie, Dionne Quan, Cheryl Chase, Tim Curry, Joe Alaskey, Tress MacNeille, Michael Bell, Melanie Chartoff, Julia Kato, Phil Proctor, Jack Riley, Tara Strong, Cree Summer, Danielle Harris, Jodi Carlisle, Lacey Chabert, Flea, Tom Kane, Bruce Willis, Tony Jay, Ethan Phillips, Chrissie Hynde, Gabriela Willer
description: The Rugrats get tangled in an exotic adventure, where they're helped by the Thornberrys, a family that travels the world making nature documentaries.

title: Rolling Thunder
cast: William Devane, Tommy Lee Jones, Linda Haynes, James Best
description: The greatest team ever, is assembled to fight the dark forces threatening our lives, our country and our world. A highly secretive, officially nonexistent unit of well-trained warriors, Roling Thunder, combines top technological know-how and high-tech equipment with superior brainpower and military might to seek out trouble and eliminite it - once and for all.

title: Rival
cast: Yelizar Nazarenko, Maria Bruni, Udo Samel
description: Nine-year-old Roman follows his mother Oksana to Germany where she is working illegally. She is living there with the 62-year-old widower Gert who suffers from diabetes. Gert tries to make friends with the boy, but Roman struggles for his mother's attention. When Oksana suddenly falls ill, Roman is left alone with his rival.

title: Resident Evil: Retribution (4K UHD)
cast: Ave Merson-O'Brian, Milla Jovovich, Michelle Rodriguez, Sally Cahill, Kevin Durand, Sienna Guillory, Shawn Roberts, Aryana Engineer, Colin Salmon, Johann Urb, Boris Kodjoe, Li Bingbing
country: Germany, Canada, United States, France, United Kingdom
description: A sequel to "Resident Evil: Afterlife 3D".

title: Resident Evil: Retribution
cast: Ave Merson-O'Brian, Milla Jovovich, Michelle Rodriguez, Sally Cahill, Kevin Durand, Sienna Guillory, Shawn Roberts, Aryana Engineer, Colin Salmon, Johann Urb, Boris Kodjoe, Li Bingbing
country: Germany, Canada, United States, France, United Kingdom
description: A sequel to "Resident Evil: Afterlife 3D".

title: Ratter
cast: Ashley Benson, Matt McGorry, Kaili Vernoff
description: A beautiful graduate student (Benson) falls prey to an insidious cyber-stalker, watching every moment from the all-seeing eyes of her phone, laptop and television.

title: Raising Arizona
cast: Nicolas Cage, Holly Hunter, Trey Wilson
description: A couple help themselves to another family's quintuplets,

title: Pumpkin
director: Adam Larson Broder, Tony R. Abrams
cast: Christina Ricci, Hank Harris, Brenda Blethyn, Dominique Swain, Marisa Coughlan, Sam Ball, Harry Lennix, Nina Foch
description: Carolyn's (Christina Ricci) sorority sisters set their sights on the Sorority of the Year award and coaching challenged athletes is their ticket to the trophy. But when the queen of formals finds herself mentoring Pumpkin (Hank Harris), a disabled athlete, their two worlds collide. Despite the hostility they feel from all sides, a tender romance grows in this inspiring comedy about fitting in.

title: Prisoners of the Sun
cast: John Rhys-Davies, David Charvet, Carmen Chaplin
description: A multinational expedition discovers a lost city beneath a pyramid, where they must stop the reawakened gods of ancient Egypt from initiating the Apocalypse.

title: Possession: The Ingloda Within
cast: Lauren Davish, Rachel Worrell
description: One girl's mysterious past leaves her with unresolved issues that begin to haunt her everyday life, while her friends try to save her from herself.

title: Pokémon the Movie 2000
description: Just one person can make a difference...

title: Play or Die
cast: Charley Palmer, Roxane Mesquida, Marie Zabukovec, Thomas Mustin, Igor Van Dessel
description: Lucas and Chloe, two passionate gamers, decide to participate in Paranoia, a very exclusive escape game. Based in a remote, abandoned mental hospital, they find four other participants waiting to play. They soon realize that only one of them will make it out alive.

title: Play
cast: Emma Bading, Oliver Masucci, Victoria Mayer, Jonas Hämmerle, Ulrike C. Tscharre, Anna Jung
description: The 17-year-old Jennifer and her parents recently moved to a new city but the shy and dreamy girl can't make friends. She takes refuge in the virtual reality of the online game 'Avalonia' and spends more and more time in the artificial world. As a result, she neglects her obligations at school and at home. Parental prohibitions do not help - the desire to play has long become a menacing addiction.

title: Pitruroon
cast: Sachin Khedekar, Tanuja, Suhas Joshi, Poorvi Bhave, Omkar Kulkarni
description: Professor Vyankatesh Kulkarni commits to fulfil his father's final wish during his last rites. A chance visit to a village brings him face to face with Sangeetappa, his look alike, and Bhagirathi, Sangeetappa's widowed mother. In his quest to figure out his father's wish, Vyankatesh finds answers to many questions he hasn't even begun to ask.

title: Pinky Moge Wali 2
cast: Gurneet Dosanjh, Neha Malik, Jimmy Sharma
description: A complicated love story between Fateh, Pinky and Roger. While Fateh is a pure Punjabi desi guy, Pinky goes to Canada for further studies. She returns after 5 years with a boyfriend, Roger. Who will she choose in the end?

title: Pack Train
cast: Gene Autry, Champion, Gail Davis
description: Gene Autry sets out to aid frontier settlers, threatened by a shortage of food and medicine. When storekeepers divert the supplies to gold miners, Gene and Smiley Burnette must ride to the rescue.

title: Ouija Japan
cast: Ariel Sekiya, Miharu Chiba, Eigi Kodaka
description: Karen, an American living in Japan, desperately wants to fit in and plays the Japanese Ouija with her peers, unwittingly disrespecting a local deity who sets her up to fight her newfound friends in a deadly game of battle royal.

title: One More Flip
cast: StreetLord Rook, Mena Monroe, Sada Baby, Tonya Hawkins, Elizbeth Foxx, Tristin Fazekas, Christopher Collins, Kaamel Hasaun, Dariss Bass, Kristin Clarke
description: A final drug deal go wrong landing Demarco Beasley in jail with no one else to turn so he turns to his girlfriend Taji adds dealing drugs already full plate.

title: Once Upon A Time In Mexico
cast: Antonio Banderas, Salma Hayek, Johnny Depp, Mickey Rourke, Eva Mendes, Danny Trejo, Enrique Iglesias, Marco Leonardi, Cheech Marin, Ruben Blades, Willem Dafoe
description: Returning from exile to avenge his slain family, the gun-slinging, guitar-toting "Desperado" dispenses justice the hard way.

title: Once Upon A Crime
cast: John Candy, James Belushi, Cybill Shepherd, George Hamilton, Giancarlo Giannini, Ornella Muti, Richard Lewis, Sean Young
description: A murder-mystery spoof in which an out-of-work actor finds a huggable little dachshund that turns out to be the hottest dog in Europe. If he can return it to Monte Carlo he'll collect a huge reward.

title: On Top Of Old Smoky
cast: Gene Autry, Champion, Gail Davis
description: Gene Autry, who is mistaken for a Texas Ranger, helps the owner of a toll road, while she is being pressured by bad characters to relinquish her property, which contains valuable mica deposits.

title: On Golden Pond
cast: Henry Fonda, Katherine Hepburn, Jane Fonda
description: In his final role, Henry Fonda plays Norman Thayer, a prickly retired professor who visits his Maine summer home with his loving wife Ethel (Hepburn). Soon, they are joined by their daughter Chelsea (Jane Fonda), her fiancé Bill, and his son Billy. Norman develops a bond with Billy, providing the framework for a summer in which the Thayers' strained relationships are finally allowed to heal.

title: Off The Lip
cast: Marguerite Moreau, Mackenzie Astin
description: A young woman's life falls apart while filming a surfing documentary.

title: Now Is the Time
description: When internationally renowned Haida carver Robert Davidson was only 22 years old, he carved the first new totem pole on British Columbia's Haida Gwaii in almost a century. On the 50th anniversary of its raising, Haida filmmaker Christopher Auchter revisits that day in August 1969, when the village of Old Massett gathered to celebrate the event that would signal the rebirth of the Haida spirit.

title: Not Like Everyone Else
cast: Alia Shawkat, Illeana Douglas, Eric Schweig
description: When a teenage girl is accused of putting a hex on a teacher, a modern day witch hunt ignites in Oklahoma.

title: No Secrets
cast: Adam Coleman Howard, Amy Locane, Heather Fairfield, Traci Lind
description: Three teenage girls – each with her own personal ""problem"" – are sent by their parents to spend spring break alone in the country, away from the city. Their solitary vacation is interrupted by the arrival of a smooth, enigmatic fugitive, who teaches each of them something about themselves.

title: Night of the Demons
cast: Shannon Elizabeth, Tatyana Kanavka, Michael Arata
description: A group of kids go to a Halloween party, only to have to face down a group of demons.

title: New Year's Evil
cast: Roz Kelly, Kip Niven, Grant Cramer, Louisa Moritz, Taaffe O'Connell, Chris Wallace, Jed Mills, Teri Copley
description: A Different Kind Of New Year's Resolution! Diane "Blaze" Sullivan, the host of a nationally televised punk-rock show on New Year's Eve, is receiving calls from a mysterious killer who tells her of his plans to off someone at midnight in each of America's major time zones and she will be the last.

title: My Story
cast: Vlastina Svátková, Pavel Kříž, Vilma Cibulková, Milan Kňažko, Stanislava Jachnická, Nela Boudová, Tereza Kostková, Zdenek Maryška, Zuzana Norisová, Jaromír Nosek, Saša Rašilov, Alžběta Staňková, Martin Stranský, Roman Vojtěk
description: Elizabeth, a flourishing ballerina, tippy toes through an abusive marriage. Her husband, an evil man, beats her up constantly until one day she mysteriously ends up in hospital barely clinging on to her life. Based on a true story, Elizabeth has to learn from scratch how to live again and, more importantly, how to love again.

title: My Name is Pauli Murray
cast: Pauli Murray, Ruth Bader Ginsburg, Patricia Bell-Scott, Dolores Chandler, Brittney Cooper
description: Overlooked by history, Pauli Murray was a legal trailblazer whose ideas influenced RBG’s fight for gender equality and Thurgood Marshall’s civil rights arguments. This is a portrait of their impact as a non-binary Black luminary: lawyer, activist, poet, and priest who transformed our world.

title: My Kingdom Come
cast: Simón González, Paqui Domínguez, Alberto Loureiro
description: SIMÓN GONZÁLEZ, a thirteen times World Spanish Kickboxing Champion; has a dream. A dream to walk again. After being the King of the World, Simón suffers a home accident that puts him in a wheel chair. But this is a story of finding hope and perseverance in the next generation of fighters. Far from hanging on to pain, Simón turned to the others finding the strength that he uses to walk again.

title: My Grandpa Is An Alien
cast: Nils Ole Oftebro, Lana Hranjec, Bill Timoney
description: The entire life of a girl named Una is turned upside down when she witnesses that her grandpa is abducted by aliens. Una, in her basement, discovers that her grandpa is an alien himself whose spaceship hit the planet some time ago, and there's still his pilot, a small grumpy robot. Una and the robot have less than 24 hours to find and rescue her grandpa.

title: Motel Hell
cast: Rory Calhoun, Nancy Parsons, Nina Axelrod, Paul Linke, Wolfman Jack, John Ratzenberger
description: Veteran actor Rory Calhoun stars as the delightfully fiendish Farmer Vincent in this deliciously ghoulish tale of the macabre that has now become a cult classic.

title: More Sex and The Single Mom
cast: Gail O'Grady, Grant Show, Chelsea Hobbs
description: Single, divorced lawyer Jess Gradwell returns in this sequal as she tries to raise her new three-year-old son, Jake, while dealing with her teenage daughter, Sara's, growing carnal desires with a photographer she meets while planning her high school graduation.

title: Mick Jagger: The Ultimate Performer
cast: Mick Jagger, Bob Geldof, Mick Taylor
description: Mick Jagger gained fame as the lead singer of the Rolling Stones. His career has spanned over five decades and he has been described as one of the most popular and influential frontmen in the history of rock and roll. This biography of the Rolling Stones front man is rich in both thoughts on Jagger from the likes of Mick Taylor and Bob Geldof as well as footage of him in action.

title: Max Bishop
cast: Chris Charais, Iris Seifert, Katie Troske, Joel Thingvall, Don Peterson, Timothy Meinke, Rachel Grubb
description: An out of work hitman finds employment as a janitor at the local elementary school.

title: Man from Del Rio
cast: Anthony Quinn, Katy Jurado, Peter Whitney, Douglas Fowley, John Larch, Whit Bissell, Douglas Spencer
description: When a Mexican gunslinger (Anthony Quinn) rids a town of several notorious gunfighters, he is named the sheriff, but must win over the rest of the residents who are yet to warm to his hard-hitting ways. Katy Jurado and Peter Whitney co-star.

title: Makoki: A Deadly Love
cast: Jeronimo Granadal, Vicky Castillo
description: The life of the best hit man in the country, Makoki, changes when he gets Chloe pregnant, a good girl with whom he will have to live for a week until his family gives him the go-ahead for the wedding and everything returns to normal .

title: Madurey
cast: Vijay, Sonia Agarwal, Rakshitha, Vadivelu, Pasupathy, Seetha, Tejashree
description: Madureyvel is a vegetable vendor and is intolerable towards injustice. He wins over many people with his good ways but unfortunately, he is blamed for a murder. Eventually, it is found that Madureyvel is no ordinary vegetable vendor. Madureyvel now tries his best to prove his innocence.

title: Madison
cast: James Caviezel, Mary McCormack, Jake Lloyd, Bruce Dern, Paul Dooley, Brent Briscoe
description: A father-son action/drama based on the inspiring true story of the tiny river town of Madison, Indiana and its legendary efforts during the hydroplane racing season of 1971. In addition to the thrills of 180-mph flat-bottomed boat racing, the picture captures the spirit of a small American river town struggling to stay alive as water transportation has virtually disappeared.

title: Lucy
cast: Rachel York, Danny Pino, Ann Dowd
description: The life story of comic genius and icon Lucille Ball depicts her rise from poverty and struggle in 1930s New York to the pinnacle of Hollywood success. Lucy finally gets her big break when she lands a television show based on her real-life marriage to dashing young Cuban bandleader Desi Arnaz. I Love Lucy would become one of the most successful and influential shows in the history of television.

title: Lovely
cast: Karthik, Malavika, Manivannan, Vivek
description: Mahadevan does not believe in love and hates the word, but his daughter Nivedha loves Chandru. In order to get his consent, the couple comes up with an intricate plan and executes it.

title: Love Letters
cast: Steven Weber, Laura Linney, Kirsten Storms
description: An ambitious U.S. Senator reflects back on his life after the death of a woman whom he loved and kept in contact with only through correspondence. The movie is told in flashbacks as the two first meet as children and begin their lifelong correspondence. He grows into his political aspirations and leaves her behind, as she becomes a struggling artist. While he is successful, she has a rocky life.

title: Love Field
cast: Michelle Pfeiffer, Dennis Haysbert, Brian Kerwin, Stephanie McFadden
description: Michelle Pfeiffer and Dennis Haybert turn in stellar performances as two strangers whose lives become irrevocably intertwined as they travel to Washington to attend President John F. Kennedy's funeral. Stephanie McFadden and Brian Kerwin also star.

title: Lost in Hong Kong
cast: Zheng Hu, Wei Zhao, Juan Du
description: Xu Lai had Dreams. He just wanted to be an Artist with a Hot Girlfriend. Now he designs bras, humors his baby-crazy wife, and caters to his loopy in-laws. But he's got a Secret Plan to find his Old Flame, and dodging his DVD-pirating, aspiring-documentarian brother-in-law may be the least of his problems. There's been a murder, and his new Hot Pursuit...might just be from the cops.
